@startuml cgs-citizen-moves-flow
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CITIZEN MOVES TO ANOTHER MUNICIPALITY — Complete CGS Flow
'  Real data from igp_ontwikkel_cgs_owner database
'  Service: StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG (29 channels, 17 providers)
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **What Happens in CGS When a Citizen Moves?**\nComplete flow from registration to all systems updated\n<size:10>Service: StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG | 29 channels | 17 provider apps | 26 authorized consumers</size>

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequenceParticipantPadding 8
skinparam sequenceBoxBorderColor #90A4AE

actor "Municipal\nEmployee" as employee #DCEDC8
participant "**iBurgerzaken**\n//Civil Affairs App//" as ibz #C8E6C9

box "CGS Service Bus — StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG" #E3F2FD
  participant "**Authorization**\n//serviceusage//" as auth #BBDEFB
  participant "**Message\nMatching**\n//messagedefinition//" as match #BBDEFB
  participant "**Transformation\nEngine**\n//993 XSLT rules//" as xform #90CAF9
  participant "**Router**\n//channeldefinition//" as router #90CAF9
  participant "**Async Queue**\n//EXACTLYONCE//" as queue #FFF59D
end box

box "ABAP Providers (SAP)" #FFF3E0
  participant "CBB\n//Taxes//" as cbb #FFE0B2
  participant "CGA\n//Addresses//" as cga #FFE0B2
  participant "CBR\n//Basic Reg.//" as cbr #FFE0B2
  participant "CZA\n//Cases//" as cza #FFE0B2
  participant "CIN\n//Collection//" as cin #FFE0B2
  participant "CKD\n//Land Reg.//" as ckd #FFE0B2
  participant "CMD\n//Resources//" as cmd #FFE0B2
  participant "CMO\n//Social Supp.//" as cmo #FFE0B2
end box

box "Java Providers" #F3E5F5
  participant "CMG\n//Broker//" as cmg #E1BEE7
  participant "CMM\n//Magazine//" as cmm #E1BEE7
end box

box "Other Providers" #ECEFF1
  participant "CWIZ\n//Social Affairs//" as cwiz #CFD8DC
  participant "GEOTAX\n//Geo-Tax//" as geotax #CFD8DC
  participant "4WOZ\n//Valuation//" as woz4 #CFD8DC
  participant "WebNext\n//Web Portal//" as webnext #CFD8DC
  participant "Legacy\n//HRS, OIS,\nBGB, WIS//" as legacy #CFD8DC
  participant "TOG\n//TOG NL//" as tog #CFD8DC
end box

== **PHASE 1: The citizen visits the municipality** ==

employee -> ibz : Registers that citizen\nJan de Vries (BSN 123456789)\nmoved from Kerkstraat 12\nto Hoofdweg 45

note over ibz
  iBurgerzaken updates BRP
  (Basisregistratie Personen)
  and needs to notify all
  other systems about the
  address change.
end note

== **PHASE 2: iBurgerzaken sends notification to CGS** ==

ibz -> auth : **SOAP Request** to:\nhttps://[server]:8443/CGS/StUF/services/BGAsynchroon\n\n**Message:** kennisgevingsBericht\n**Namespace:** http://www.egem.nl/StUF/sector/bg/0204\n**Entity type:** NPS (Natuurlijk Persoon)\n**Contains:** old address + new address + BSN
note right of auth
  **Message type = npsLk01**
  (Natuurlijk Persoon Lk01 = 
  Person change notification)
  
  StUF-BG format 0204
  Async handling
end note

== **PHASE 3: CGS Authorization Check** ==

auth -> auth : SELECT * FROM serviceusage\nWHERE application_id = <iBurgerzaken>\nAND servicedefinition_id = <StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG>
note right of auth
  **26 apps authorized** for this service:
  iBurgerzaken, CBB, CGA, CBR, CZA,
  CIN, CKD, CMD, CMG, CMO, CWIZ,
  FrontOffice, SquitXO, ZGS_SSL...
  
  ✅ iBurgerzaken is authorized
end note

auth --> ibz : **Bv04Bericht** (StUF 0301)\n//"Message received, will be processed"//
note left of ibz
  **Immediate confirmation!**
  iBurgerzaken can continue
  working. CGS handles
  delivery in background.
end note

== **PHASE 4: Message Matching** ==

auth -> match : Forward kennisgevingsBericht
match -> match : Match by namespace + messagekey:\n\n**namespace** = ""http://www.egem.nl/StUF/sector/bg/0204""\n**messagekey** = ""kennisgevingsBericht/stuurgegevens/entiteittype""\n**entity** = NPS\n\n→ Matched to: **BG 0204 kennisgevingsBericht**

note right of match
  **40 possible BG message types:**
  npsLk01 (person), aoaLk01 (address),
  vbtLk01 (residence), oprLk01 (public space),
  pndLk01 (building), wplLk01 (city),
  gemLk01 (municipality), ...
  
  For a move: **npsLk01** (person change)
  with address data in the payload
end note

== **PHASE 5: Transformation Check** ==

match -> xform : Message matched, check format needs

xform -> xform : Check all 29 channels:\nDo any providers need a different format?

note right of xform
  **Available transformations for this message:**
  
  • **BG 0204 → BG 0210** (Centric variant)
    "Upgrade van BG 2.04 naar BG 2.10"
    For apps that speak the Centric dialect
    
  • **BG 0210 → BG 0204** (downgrade)
    "Downgrade van BG 2.10 naar BG 2.04"
    For legacy systems
    
  • **BG 0204 → BG 0310** (new standard)
    For modern StUF-BG applications
    
  In this environment most channels
  receive **0204 natively** — no
  transformation needed for most.
  
  **Bv04 → Bv03**: response transformation
  applied when channel expects Bv03
  confirmation instead of Bv04.
end note

== **PHASE 6: Dynamic Routing — The Fan-out** ==

xform -> router : Message ready (original + transformed copies)

router -> router : SELECT * FROM channeldefinition\nWHERE servicedefinition_id = <StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG>\nAND active = true\n\n→ **29 active channels found!**

note over router
  **Channel selection criteria (AND logic):**
  1. filterprovidingapplication_id → which provider app?
  2. filtermessagedefinition_id → only specific message types?
  3. active = true → channel enabled?
  
  **Result: message is copied to ALL 29 channels**
  Each channel targets a specific provider + endpoint
end note

== **PHASE 7: Queue & Delivery — Each Provider Gets Its Copy** ==

router -> queue : Place 29 copies in sending queue\n(QoS = EXACTLYONCE = guaranteed delivery)
note right of queue
  **Check applicationopeningperiod:**
  Is each target app currently "open"?
  • Open → deliver now
  • Closed → hold until opening
end note

|||

queue -[#E65100,bold]> cbb : **Channel → CBB**\nEndpoint: CBB\nProtocol: **ABAP** (SAP JCo)\nFormat: StUF BG 0204\nNo transformation needed
queue -[#E65100,bold]> cga : **Channel → CGA**\nEndpoint: CGA\nProtocol: **ABAP**\nFormat: StUF BG 0204
queue -[#E65100,bold]> cbr : **Channel → CBR**\nEndpoints: CBR + CBRA\nProtocol: **ABAP** (2 channels)
queue -[#E65100,bold]> cza : **Channel → CZA**\nEndpoint: CZA\nProtocol: **ABAP**
queue -[#E65100]> cin : **Channel → CIN**\nProtocol: **ABAP**
queue -[#E65100]> ckd : **Channel → CKD**\nProtocol: **ABAP**
queue -[#E65100]> cmd : **Channel → CMD**\nProtocol: **ABAP**
queue -[#E65100]> cmo : **Channel → CMO**\nProtocol: **ABAP**
queue -[#6A1B9A,bold]> cmg : **Channels → CMG** (4 channels)\nEndpoint: CMG\nProtocol: **Java** (internal JVM)
queue -[#6A1B9A]> cmm : **Channels → CMM** (4 channels)\nEndpoints: CMMSTUFASYN\nProtocol: **Java**
queue -[#546E7A]> cwiz : **Channel → CWIZ**\nEndpoint: CSAMUNIFACE\nProtocol: **UNIFACE** (via STUNNEL)
queue -[#2E7D32]> geotax : **Channel → GEOTAX**\nEndpoint: GEOTAX\nProtocol: **WEBSERVICE** (SOAP)
queue -[#2E7D32]> woz4 : **Channel → 4WOZ**\nEndpoint: 4WOZ\nProtocol: **WEBSERVICE**
queue -[#0D47A1]> webnext : **Channel → WebNext**\nEndpoint: (HTTP)\nProtocol: **HTTP**
queue -[#2E7D32]> legacy : **Channels → Legacy** (4 channels)\nEndpoints: HRSSTUFASYN,\nOISSTUFASYN, BGBSTUFASYN,\nWISSTUFASYN\nProtocol: **WEBSERVICE**
queue -[#2E7D32]> tog : **Channel → TOG**\nProtocol: **WEBSERVICE**

== **PHASE 8: Each System Processes the Move** ==

note over cbb
  **CBB (Taxes)**
  Recalculates tax
  obligation based
  on new address.
  New municipality →
  new tax rates.
end note

note over cga
  **CGA (Addresses)**
  Updates address
  registration.
  Links person to
  new address object.
end note

note over cbr
  **CBR (Basic Reg.)**
  Updates person's
  official registration
  record with new
  residential address.
end note

note over cmg
  **CMG (Broker)**
  Updates the central
  data store (magazine).
  Makes new address
  available for all
  future queries.
end note

note over cwiz
  **CWIZ (Social)**
  Checks if person
  has active social
  benefits that need
  address update.
end note

note over geotax
  **GEOTAX**
  Updates geo-spatial
  tax mapping for
  the new address.
end note

== **PHASE 9: Follow-up — Other Apps Query the New Address** ==

note over auth, queue
  **After the async fan-out, other services trigger:**
  
  When apps need the person's **current** data, they call **StUFBeantwoordVraagBG** (synchronous):
  
  • REQUEST: vraagBericht (StUF BG 0204) — "Give me the data of person X"
  • CGS routes to: **CGS** (Java) → **CML** (Java) → **CMM** (Java Magazine)
  • RESPONSE: synchroonAntwoordBericht — new address included
  
  This way, the Portal, FrontOffice, or any third-party app
  that queries citizen data will automatically get the new address.
end note

@enduml


@startuml cgs-citizen-moves-overview
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
'  CITIZEN MOVES — Simplified Overview
'  Bird's eye view of all systems affected
' ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

title **Citizen Moves — All Affected Systems at a Glance**\n//One address change triggers updates in 17 applications across 5 protocols//

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 15
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam nodesep 30
skinparam ranksep 25

' === THE EVENT ===
actor "Citizen" as citizen
component "**iBurgerzaken**\nRegisters the move\nat the municipality" as ibz #C8E6C9

citizen -right-> ibz : "I moved from\nKerkstraat 12\nto Hoofdweg 45"

' === CGS ===
package "**CGS Service Bus**" as cgs #E3F2FD {
  component "**StUFOntvangAsynchroonBG**\n\n//Service: Async BG Notifications//\n//Handling: ASYN / EXACTLYONCE//\n//29 routing channels//\n\n**Message in:** kennisgevingsBericht\n  namespace: StUF/sector/bg/0204\n  entity: NPS (person change)\n\n**Response:** Bv04Bericht (immediate)\n**Fault:** Fo03Bericht (on error)" as svc #BBDEFB
}

ibz -down-> svc : **SOAP** via ABAP adapter\nnpsLk01 (person notification)\nStUF-BG 0204 format

' === PROVIDERS GROUPED BY PROTOCOL ===

package "**ABAP / SAP JCo** — 8 apps, 10 channels" as abap_grp #FFF3E0 {
  component "**CBB** //Taxes//\nRecalculate tax for new address" as p_cbb #FFE0B2
  component "**CGA** //Addresses//\nUpdate address registration" as p_cga #FFE0B2
  component "**CBR** //Basic Reg.//\nUpdate person record (2 ch)" as p_cbr #FFE0B2
  component "**CZA** //Cases//\nUpdate active case addresses" as p_cza #FFE0B2
  component "**CIN** //Collection//\nUpdate collection records" as p_cin #FFE0B2
  component "**CKD** //Land Registry//\nUpdate cadastral links" as p_ckd #FFE0B2
  component "**CMD** //Resources//\nUpdate resource allocation" as p_cmd #FFE0B2
  component "**CMO** //Social Support//\nUpdate social care records" as p_cmo #FFE0B2
}

package "**Java** (internal JVM) — 2 apps, 8 channels" as java_grp #F3E5F5 {
  component "**CMG** //Broker Data// (4 ch)\nUpdate central data store\nFuture queries return new address" as p_cmg #E1BEE7
  component "**CMM** //Magazine// (4 ch)\nUpdate data magazine\nSync with CMG" as p_cmm #E1BEE7
}

package "**UNIFACE** — 1 app, 1 channel" as uni_grp #FFECB3 {
  component "**CWIZ** //Social Affairs//\nUpdate benefits & social records\nvia STUNNEL proxy" as p_cwiz #FFE082
}

package "**WEBSERVICE / SOAP** — 5 apps, 7 channels" as ws_grp #E8F5E9 {
  component "**GEOTAX** //Geo-Tax//\nUpdate spatial tax map" as p_geotax #C8E6C9
  component "**4WOZ** //Valuation//\nUpdate property valuation links" as p_4woz #C8E6C9
  component "**TOG** //TOG Nederland//\nUpdate external registry" as p_tog #C8E6C9
  component "**Legacy** //HRS, OIS, BGB, WIS// (4 ch)\nUpdate legacy PinkRoccade systems" as p_legacy #C8E6C9
}

package "**HTTP** — 1 app, 1 channel" as http_grp #FCE4EC {
  component "**WebNext** //Web Portal//\nUpdate online citizen portal\nNew address visible to citizen" as p_webnext #F8BBD0
}

' === DELIVERY CONNECTIONS ===
svc -[#E65100,bold]-> p_cbb
svc -[#E65100,bold]-> p_cga
svc -[#E65100]-> p_cbr
svc -[#E65100]-> p_cza
svc -[#E65100]-> p_cin
svc -[#E65100]-> p_ckd
svc -[#E65100]-> p_cmd
svc -[#E65100]-> p_cmo

svc -[#6A1B9A,bold]-> p_cmg
svc -[#6A1B9A]-> p_cmm

svc -[#FF8F00,bold]-> p_cwiz

svc -[#2E7D32]-> p_geotax
svc -[#2E7D32]-> p_4woz
svc -[#2E7D32]-> p_tog
svc -[#2E7D32]-> p_legacy

svc -[#AD1457]-> p_webnext

' === FOLLOW-UP SYNC QUERY ===
package "**Follow-up: Sync Queries**\n(StUFBeantwoordVraagBG)" as sync_box #FFFDE7 {
  component "Any app can now **ask** for\ncitizen data and will get\nthe **new address** back.\n\n//vraagBericht → CGS → CMM//\n//→ synchroonAntwoordBericht//" as sync_note #FFF9C4
}

p_cmm .down.> sync_note : CMM now has\nnew address
p_cmg .down.> sync_note : CMG provides\nquery results

note bottom of svc
  **Transformation Engine (if needed):**
  
  Most channels receive StUF BG **0204** natively.
  If a channel needs a different format:
  
  • **BG 0204 → 0210**: "Upgrade" to Centric variant
  • **BG 0204 → 0310**: "Upgrade" to new standard
  • **BG 0210 → 0204**: "Downgrade" from Centric
  • **Bv04 → Bv03**: Transform response confirmation
  
  993 XSLT stylesheets available for all
  StUF entity types (person, address,
  building, municipality, etc.)
end note

@enduml
